Reference https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array

checking if given variable is an array use isArray
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/isArray


Array.copyWithin(target, start, end)
This copies the array to itself,
the target is where it should start copying from,
start and end are what parts of the array to copy ie subset of the array to copy
end is excluded
the array is modified


Array.fill(value, start, end)
fills the array with value from start to end

Array.pop()
removes last value from the array

Array.sort(compareFunction)
compare function should take two parameters and return either -1,0,1
sort compares all the values based on the sort function like
if a, b are the two parameters then if function returns
-1 then it assumes a>b
0 a== b
1 a<b
this updates the array


Array.splice(start, number , item1, item2 ...)
splice starts from start and removes the number  of items from the array and add the item1, item2 ... there

Array.unshift()
add elements to the beginning of array just like push but reverse